verbatimAttributes: Flower diameter 40-50 mm, 23-27 mm long, stigma lobes 4-6, yellow, outer perianth light to medium fuschia, inner perianth light to medium fuschia, bright orange, very colorful flower, with magenta anthers. Spines cluster: basal spines form a circle at top of tubercule and are white, other extending spines are golden or reddish, stem color noted as yellow-green; no ribs present.
locality: In cultivation Desert Botanical Garden, Phoenix, Maricopa Co, AZ, lat 33.461395, lon -111.944487, ele 1280' bed 47; accession number 1981-0212-01-1, received from SL Benson from Texas, Terrell Co., 5 miles west of Sanderson.

verbatimAttributes: Plant height 15.5 cm, width 6 cm taken at widest point which is half way up stem; stem single, columnar-barrel, shiny green with ribs swirling around, two stem buds; radial spines 8, white, tan or taupe with black tips; single central spine dark reddish-brown, longer than radial spines; flowers collected late morning to early afternoon, additional flowers collected in April 2022; flower diameter (40-closing) 46-57 mm, length 23-30 mm; outer perianth pale magenta-pink with a greenish-brown midstripe; inner perianth magenta with pale golden at very base of tepals; stigma lobe number 4-5, white or pale yellow; style white; filaments white; anthers golden yellow.
locality: Grown in cultivation at Desert Botanical Garden, Phoenix, N 33 deg 27' 33'', W 111 deg 56' 35'', 1200 ft, 366 m: accession number 1994-0307-01-1; originally received as a plant collected by Edward F. Anderson 5042, 27 July 1979 from Texas, Terrell County, 1 mile east of Sanderson; 2.5 miles east of junction 90 & 285; collector's notes: Associated species - Chihuahuan Desert Scrub; habitat and soil - Large limestone hills NE of the hwy, Rio Grande drainage.

verbatimAttributes: Single barrel to cylindrical, upright stem, height 11 cm, width 8 cm; rib count 9, areoles somewhat tuberculate, stem color dark green; spines angled, light gray with darker tips, 6-7 per areole; single flower collected mid-morning, diameter 28 mm, length 78 mm; outer perianth reddish magenta with a darker burgundy midstripe; inner perianth coral; stigma lobe number 10, color green; style white; anthers purple or mauve. Plant is listed as DEAD in February 2013, unable to locate in bed 0-42A and assumed dead; last living inventory May 1998.
